# Backfill Shifts — AI Re-Architecture Engineering Package

## Document purpose

This document assumes **Backfill Shifts already exists** as defined in the prior engineering package.

This package describes how to **re-architect the existing product into an AI-native action system** where:

* voice,
* SMS,
* and([docs.retellai.com](https://docs.retellai.com/build/single-multi-prompt/custom-function))all use the same underlying scheduling and coverage action layer.

This is **not** a rewrite of the base product. It is a layered re-architecture that turns the existing product into an AI-powered operating system with channel-specific guardrails.

---

# 1) Strategic product decision

## New product posture

Backfill Shifts is no longer just:

* a text-first scheduling UI,
* plus callout automation,
* plus a coverage engine.

It becomes:

**an AI-native scheduling and coverage action platform with multiple control surfaces.**

Those control surfaces are:

* Voice via Retell agents over the phone number
* SMS via the same number and agent stack
* Web via a native Backfill AI prompt layer built inside Backfill Shifts

## Core principle

The AI does not directly mutate schedules, roster state, or coverage state by improvisation.

Instead, every request is translated into a **typed action plan** that runs through:

1. intent detection
2. entity resolution
3. policy and permission checks
4. confirmation rules
5. execution against canonical APIs/services
6. audit logging
7. user-facing result communication

The product is therefore re-centered around a **shared action orchestration layer** rather than around UI workflows alone.

