# 2) Architectural shift

## Previous architecture

The existing product likely behaves roughly like this:

* Web UI directly calls scheduling APIs
* Retell voice flows call webhooks for callouts
* SMS/phone behavior is somewhat workflow-specific
* Manager actions are still modeled primarily as UI interactions

## New architecture

All three channels become clients of a common orchestration stack:

### Channel surfaces

* Retell Voice Agent
* Retell SMS/Chat Agent on the business number
* Native Web Prompt Window inside Backfill Shifts
* Existing structured web UI

### Shared AI/action stack

* Intent Router
* Entity Resolver
* Action Planner
* Risk/Confirmation Engine
* Policy & Permissions Engine
* Canonical Action Executor
* Audit/Event Writer
* Result Renderer

### Existing domain services reused underneath

* roster service
* schedule service
* shift service
* publish/amend service
* enrollment service
* messaging service
* coverage engine
* analytics/audit service

## Key rule

**No channel talks directly to domain mutation services without going through the action orchestration rules when the request originated in natural language.**

Structured UI interactions may still call canonical APIs directly.

