# 5) Channel capability matrix

## Voice — allowed actions

### Green (auto-execute when high confidence)

* employee callout reporting
* manager asking “who is unfilled tomorrow?”
* manager asking “publish the current draft” if there is only one valid draft
* manager asking for schedule summary/status

### Yellow (confirmation required)

* remove an employee from a specific shift
* open a specific shift
* approve an identified employee claim
* create a single shift when date/time/location/role are clear

### Red (redirect to web prompt or structured UI)

* bulk schedule rebuilds
* recurring rule changes
* multi-location edits
* mass employee edits
* anything with broad blast radius or ambiguous resolution

## SMS — allowed actions

### Green

* publish schedule
* copy last week
* schedule summary requests
* who is unfilled / what changed / what is at risk
* create a simple shift when unambiguous
* remove an employee from a specific shift when unambiguous
* open a shift
* approve or deny a fill

### Yellow

* shift swaps
* move shifts across dates or locations
* create multiple shifts in one instruction
* reassignment where multiple employees or shifts match
* send offers to all qualified workers

### Red

* bulk roster changes
* policy/rule changes
* major rewrites
* anything that benefits from diff preview

## Web AI prompt — allowed actions

### Green

* most single-entity schedule and shift edits
* conflict explanations
* generating draft schedules
* filtering and summarizing schedule issues
* approving recommended fixes

### Yellow

* multi-step schedule rewrites
* staff redistribution across several shifts
* edits with overtime or fairness tradeoffs
* changes affecting many employees but still previewable

### Red

* permissions/billing/security changes
* destructive account-level operations without explicit structured confirmation

