# 6) New system components to introduce

## 6.1 Intent Router

### Purpose

Accept natural-language requests from voice, SMS, or web prompt and classify them into one of:

* query
* command
* workflow initiation
* clarification response
* confirmation response
* cancellation

### Responsibilities

* classify user intent
* determine target domain (schedule, shift, roster, coverage, publish, query)
* pass request to resolver/planner

## 6.2 Entity Resolver

### Purpose

Resolve names, shifts, dates, locations, roles, and schedule references from natural-language input.

### Responsibilities

* resolve employee names (“Randy”)
* resolve date references (“tomorrow night”, “next Friday”)
* resolve shift references (“the closing shift”, “Randy’s shift”)
* resolve location references
* detect ambiguity and produce candidates

### Required outputs

* exact match
* ranked candidates
* confidence score
* clarification prompts if needed

## 6.3 Action Planner

### Purpose

Translate resolved user request into a typed action plan.

### Example

User says:

> “Create me a new shift with Randy off the schedule.”

Planner output might be:

* action A: remove Randy from shift_id=123
* action B: mark shift open
* action C: trigger coverage workflow
* risk class: yellow
* confirmation required: yes

## 6.4 Risk and Confirmation Engine

### Purpose

Decide whether a request can:

* auto-execute,
* execute after confirmation,
* or must redirect to web preview/manual review.

### Inputs

* action type
* number of entities affected
* ambiguity score
* user role/permission
* schedule lifecycle state
* downstream blast radius

## 6.5 Policy and Permissions Engine

### Purpose

Ensure natural-language requests do not bypass normal product permissions or business rules.

### Responsibilities

* validate actor role
* check location scope
* check publish rights
* check whether action is allowed over channel
* check whether action requires structured confirmation

## 6.6 Canonical Action Executor

### Purpose

Execute approved action plans against existing domain services.

### Key rule

This layer must call the same services/APIs that the structured UI uses so AI actions and manual UI actions remain consistent.

## 6.7 Result Renderer

### Purpose

Render the result appropriately by channel.

### Examples

* Voice: concise spoken confirmation
* SMS: short summary with optional confirmation CTA
* Web: detailed result card + diff + deep links

