# 13) Voice product changes

## Retell remains the phone surface

Retell custom functions/webhooks should continue to be used for phone actions.

## Expand voice beyond employee callouts — selectively

Voice should support:

* employee callouts
* manager status questions
* simple approval actions
* simple shift operations with confirmation

## Voice should not become the full admin surface

Avoid using voice for:

* bulk schedule rewrites
* high-ambiguity shift operations without confirmation
* major roster changes
* deep multi-location management

## Voice agent behavior requirement

Retell should call the shared action orchestration endpoints, not bespoke callout-only endpoints, except where the endpoint is still a typed action endpoint under the same orchestration layer.

