# 17) New UX rules for AI actions

## Rule 1 — explain what will happen

Before yellow or red actions, the system must restate the planned change.

## Rule 2 — always show affected entities

Manager should see:

* which shift(s)
* which employee(s)
* which date(s)
* which location(s)

## Rule 3 — support undo where practical

At minimum, amended schedule changes should be reversible through existing amendment/version mechanics.

## Rule 4 — ambiguous requests never silently execute

Any unresolved ambiguity must trigger clarification or redirect.

## Rule 5 — natural language does not bypass permissioning

The same role limits apply whether the user clicked a button or sent a prompt.

